Name:           Ebnf2ps
Version:        1.0.15
Release:        0
Summary:        Peter's Syntax Diagram Drawing Tool
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  ghc-array-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-containers-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-directory-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-old-time-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-unix-devel
BuildRequires:  happy

%description
Ebnf2ps generates nice looking syntax diagrams in EPS and FIG format from EBNF
specifications and from yacc, bison, and Happy input grammars. The diagrams can
be immediatedly included in TeX/LaTeX documents and in texts created with other
popular document preparation systems.


